text: Patissa rubrilinealis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found in Malawi. The wingspan is about 12 mm. The forewings are silvery white with a scarlet medial line from below the costa to the inner margin. The hindwings are silvery white.Annals and Magazine of Natural History (9) 4 (23): 318 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa rubrilinealis
